@node "GUI" "Usage of the GUI"

I think the GUI is pretty intuitive to use, so I will not discuss in detail.
If you have installed the Guide in a proper place in your Amigaguide Path
you can get online help pressing the HELP key.

I give you here an overview which GUI element which smake option corresponds:

- DEBUG: You have to add a DEBUG variable to your smakefile (see the @{"Smakefile" link "src/Smakefile/main"}
  in the src directory for an example (this link only works if you have the
  src directory in the same directory like this guide)) to be able to use
  this option. It adds the variable DEBUG="DEBUG full" to the command line
  thus replacing your empty defined variable.

- SMAKE DEBUG: corresponds -d switch of smake

- ALL: corresponds -a switch of smake

- SILENT: corresponds -s switch of smake

- ERASE: corresponds -e switch of smake

- SMAKE FILE: corresponds -f <filename> switch of smake

- TARGET NAME: this name will be added at the end of the call thus telling
  Smake to use this target name instead of the default.

- DEFAULT FILE: corresponds -b <filename> switch of smake

- SAVE: Save the options under the filename "smopts"

- CANCEL: Hmm, ???

@endnode

@node "Technical" "Technical Data :-)"

Technical hints
---------------

The GUI itself has been designed using BGUIBuilder V0.91beta. I simply
had to integrate the ready GUI in my source code. This program makes
makeing @{"BGUI" link "BGUI"} GUIs really easy :-). The program uses parts from _main.c
(source code delievered with SAS/C) for reading the smopts file. I
created a datatype to hold the switches and it arguments (if there are
any). I have not tested it but it could be possible that you can compile
progam with DICE as well. I have no idea for GCC (mainly concerning the
tooltypes). If you're interested in these and have solutions send
some patches to me.

If you want to recompile it you need to copy the bgui.lib to sc:lib/ so the
linker can find it. The lib only opens the BGUI.library (I'm a lazy man ;)

If you want me to add rexx scripts and/or prefs file for other editors like
GED, XDME, Emacs or whatever which you have created please send them to me.
(You will get some credits in return :-).

BGUIBuilder automatically uses the stringpatch (which corrects a bug in
Intuition Integer Gadgets) and so I included it though the program does
not make use of it itself. Read the Smakefile for further information.

This Guide, the program and all additionally text files have been written
with BED (by Marco Negri). It can be found on Aminet.

@endnode

